item.title: What is frame 126?
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

Frame 126 is anything that’s editable text. For example, something like "“Level 80: Charge” or “Dragon Slayer”, or even emotes like “Yes” and “No.”

To change what the text says for any line like I showed you, you use this method:

sendFrame126("New Frame Text", ID);

Replace New Frame Text with the text you want to replace, and replace ID with the ID of the frame. You may dump the IDs or use an ID list that has already been released. I’ve downloaded one in my time here, and I’ve attached it to this post. Feel free to use it. Credits go to Called Enzo.
